Image Widget

The image widget is inserted into a document to display one or more selected images. It consist of the following 2 sections: Images section and Comments (Annotations) section. The image section is above the comments section by default.

 

Note: To see how to insert and configure the widget look 

View Images

 

Different views of the image widget are available. You can select from:

  • Image view
  • Book view
  • Scroll View
  • Gallery View

Add slot

 

  1. New slots can be added for image comparison purposes at the left, right, top or bottom.
  2.  New images can be added in the added slot.
  3.  Click Close to remove the slot.

Annotate the image

 

  1. Select the action "Annotate" in tools.
  2. Selects the option to annotate.
  3. Choose the shape.
  4. Select the area.
  5. The pop up for adding new comment opens.
  6. Enter the text of the comment.
  7. Click Save.

Review annotations

 

Annotations are presented in the comment section of the Image widget.
 

Scale Bar

 

When the user zooms in/ zooms out of images for which there is information for the physical dimensions of the image, a scale bar (ruler) in the image shows the distance in units proportional to the image scale.

  1. There is scale bar in the image widget only for images for which there is information for the physical dimensions in the properties "Width of Subject" and "Unit".
  2.  The scale bar is positioned at the bottom left corner of the image in the image widget.
  3. The default unit system in the scale bar is metric.
